Went for a familiar yet new and refreshing vibe on this one. Focused less on filling the frequency spectrum and more on the telling of the story.

Wanted to note that ‘Lightfall’ was entirely inspired by @mike.mascioli and @fivecentcity. This whole idea came to fruition when we were brainstorming ideas to work together to provide quality musical entertainment at Five Cent City’s final year this year. After having heard Mike’s demo titled “Lightfall”, I immediately felt the need to try creating something of my own by using all of the beautiful and complex melodies he came up with for the track.
•
Luckily, I shortly after stumbled across this vocal that fit the emotion I was aiming for perfectly. An urban, pop-like vocal that talks about the struggles of changing. However, rather than interpreting the lyrics as being spoken from an individual struggling with heartbreak, I use them to tell the story of somebody battling within themselves to implement a change they so desperately desire. That ‘float-y’ type feeling I went for in the drop was my way of enacting someone breaking through that barrier of struggle, and finally taking that first step towards whatever goal or change they aspire for. Something that resonates with myself all too well.
•
So yeah, I hope this song makes you feel like you’re floating in a transcendental space where any change you strive for is within reach. Or you know, just makes your day even the slightest bit better 👊🏼
•
